compared with $1.079 billion in the fourth quarter of 2018. The increase was mostly due to lower SG&A/R&D expenses, primarily
due to a reduction in short-term incentive compensation expense and lower R&D project expenses. Lower manufacturing costs
were mostly offset by lower sales volume.
