Recognition of income is suspended and the finance receivable is placed on non-accrual status when management determines
that collection of future income is not probable (generally after 120 days past due).  Recognition is resumed and previously
suspended income is recognized when the finance receivable becomes current and collection of remaining amounts is
considered probable. Payments received while the finance receivable is on non-accrual status are applied to interest and
principal in accordance with the contractual terms.
 
