Troubled Debt Restructurings
 
A restructuring of a finance receivable constitutes a troubled debt restructuring (TDR) when the lender grants a concession it
would not otherwise consider to a borrower experiencing financial difficulties.  Concessions granted may include extended
contract maturities, inclusion of interest only periods, below market interest rates, extended skip payment periods and
reduction of principal and/or accrued interest.
 
