1 Effective December 31, 2019, all U.S. pension benefits were frozen, and accordingly this assumption is no longer applicable.
The assumed discount rate is used to discount future benefit obligations back to today’s dollars.  The U.S. discount rate is
based on a benefit cash flow-matching approach and represents the rate at which our benefit obligations could effectively be
settled as of our measurement date, December 31.  The benefit cash flow-matching approach involves analyzing Caterpillar’s
projected cash flows against a high quality bond yield curve, calculated using a wide population of corporate Aa bonds
available on the measurement date.  A similar process is used to determine the assumed discount rate for our most significant
non-U.S. plans. This rate is sensitive to changes in interest rates. A decrease in the discount rate would increase our obligation
and future expense.
